<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="1540" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="27.[178,1086,549,695]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540">
D i a g n o s i s: Distinguishable from superficially similar specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="OPITZ" authorityYear="2015" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pilosirus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amazonicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540">Pilosirus amazonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having much narrower flavotestaceous lines on the pronotal disc. Also, the pronotal tubercle is more acute than it is in 
<emphasis box="[687,806,644,665]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540">amazonicus</emphasis>
specimens (compare 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 133-144" captionStartId="40.[178,218,1358,1380]" captionTargetBox="[207,1052,231,1340]" captionTargetId="figure-1@40.[178,1084,212,1340]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="Figs 133-144: Aedeagi (133-140), Pronota (141-142), and Female mesodermal female reproductive organs (143-144). (133) Artoadenus similus phallus; (134) A. similus tegmen; (135) Tarandocerus auratus phallus; (136) T. auratus tegmen; (137) T. mexicanus phallus; (138) T. mexicanus tegmen; (139) T. testaceiceps phallus; (140) T. testaceiceps tegmen; (141) Pilosirus amazonicus; (142) P. versus; (143) Ambonoides retinoides female internal reproductive organs; (144) A. retinoides bursal plate." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5294880" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5294880/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540">Figs. 141, 142</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[178,1086,710,937]" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Size: Length 7.0 mm; width 2.0 mm. Form: As in 
<figureCitation box="[920,1009,710,732]" captionStart="Figs 161-164" captionStartId="52.[178,218,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,212,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-59@52.[178,1085,212,1498]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="Figs 161-164: Habitus illustrations of (161) Pilosirus fasciatus, holotype; (162) P. versus, holotype; (163) Platynoptera carti, holotype; (164) Platynoptera flavohumeralis, holotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5282519" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5282519/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540">Fig. 162</figureCitation>
. Color: Cranium mostly black, clypeus and cranial venter flavotestaceous; pronotum mostly black, upper sides narrowly flavotestaceous; mesoscutellum black; elytra black. Head: Antennal capitulum long (
<figureCitation box="[448,525,798,820]" captionStart="Figs 81-86" captionStartId="22.[178,218,1223,1245]" captionTargetBox="[192,1067,240,1173]" captionTargetId="figure-1@22.[178,1085,212,1205]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figs 81-86: Antennae. (81) Platynoptera ochreata, female; (82) Artoadenus similus, male; (83) Tarandocerus auratus, male; (84) T. mexicanus, male; (85) T. testaceiceps, male; (86) Pilosirus versus, female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5294868" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5294868/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="1540">Fig. 86</figureCitation>
), each capitular antennomere not as long as combined length of funicular antennomeres; antennal carina very prominent; EW/FW 12/15. Thorax: Pronotal anterior margin not projected at middle, side margin of disc with subacute tubercle; PW/PL 45/45; elytral disc not strongly deflexed at sides, carina not present; EL/EW 160/30. Abdomen: Female pygidium not incised at distal margin.
</paragraph>
